83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
HOUSE AMENDMENTS TO
A-ENGROSSED HOUSE BILL 4016
By JOINT COMMITTEE ON WAYS AND MEANS
March 3
1 On page 4 of the printed A-engrossed bill, delete lines 8 through 13 and insert:
2 “(e) Is not in violation of any tax laws described in ORS 305.380. If the anticipated price of a
3 public contract that a contracting agency awards or renews is $250,000 or less, the bidder or
4 proposer shall demonstrate compliance by attesting to the bidder’s or proposer’s compliance in any
5 manner the contracting agency deems credible and convenient. If the anticipated price of a public
6 contract that a state contracting agency awards or renews is more than $250,000, the bidder or
7 proposer shall submit to the state contracting agency a certificate from the Department of Revenue,
8 as provided in ORS 305.385 (6).”.
9 On page 5, after line 13, insert:
10 “SECTION 7. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the General Fund appropriation
11 made to the Department of Revenue by section 1 (3), chapter 553, Oregon Laws 2025, for the
12 biennium ending June 30, 2027, for the Personal Tax and Compliance Division, is increased
13 by $262,503, for the purpose of carrying out section 2 of this 2026 Act.
14 “SECTION 8. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expenditures, the limitation on
15 expenditures established by section 2 (3), chapter 553, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium
16 ending June 30, 2027, as the maximum limit for payment of expenses from fees, moneys or
17 other revenues, including Miscellaneous Receipts and reimbursements from federal service
18 agreements, but excluding lottery funds and federal funds not described in section 2, chapter
19 553, Oregon Laws 2025, collected or received by the Department of Revenue, for the Personal
20 Tax and Compliance Division, is increased by $6,358, for the purpose of carrying out section
21 2 of this 2026 Act.
22 “SECTION 9. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the General Fund appropriation
23 made to the Department of Revenue by section 1 (4), chapter 553, Oregon Laws 2025, for the
24 biennium ending June 30, 2027, for the Business Division, is increased by $41,928, for the
25 purpose of carrying out section 2 of this 2026 Act.
26 “SECTION 10. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expenditures, the limitation on
27 expenditures established by section 2 (4), chapter 553, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium
28 ending June 30, 2027, as the maximum limit for payment of expenses from fees, moneys or
29 other revenues, including Miscellaneous Receipts and reimbursements from federal service
30 agreements, but excluding lottery funds and federal funds not described in section 2, chapter
31 553, Oregon Laws 2025, collected or received by the Department of Revenue, for the Business
32 Division, is increased by $42,626, for the purpose of carrying out section 2 of this 2026 Act.
33 “SECTION 11. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the General Fund appropri-
34 ation made to the Department of Revenue by section 1 (5), chapter 553, Oregon Laws 2025,
35 for the biennium ending June 30, 2027, for the Collections Division, is increased by $44,417,
